{
  "texts": [
    "Observers located there will see the source light coming from two directions in their sky.",
    "The rays near the middle of Fig. 2 undergo very large deflections, even more than 180 •.",
    "Large deflections occur in strong gravitational fields near neutron stars and black holes, leading to the exotic multiple imaging now observed near the M87 black hole (Broderick et al. 2022).",
    "It does not, however, occur in the systems we will consider.",
    "Fig. 2 A representation of the deflection of light rays."
  ]
}